### Shared UI Primitives

These components are at [`app/components/`](app/components/) root and are used across all domains:

| Component | Props Pattern | Usage |
|-----------|--------------|-------|
| [`Button`](app/components/Button.tsx) | `variant`, `loading`, `to` (link mode) | Forms, actions, navigation |
| [`Card`](app/components/Card.tsx) | `title`, `subtitle`, `actions`, `children` | Data display containers |
| [`Badge`](app/components/Badge.tsx) | `variant` (`success`, `warning`, `danger`, `info`) | Status indicators |
| [`DataTable`](app/components/DataTable.tsx) | Generic `<T>`, `columns`, `data`, `keyExtractor` | Tabular data with sort/filter |
| [`DatePicker`](app/components/DatePicker.tsx) | `value`, `onChange`, `label` | Date selection |
| [`EmptyState`](app/components/EmptyState.tsx) | `title`, `description`, `action` | Empty/no-data states |
| [`Pagination`](app/components/Pagination.tsx) | `page`, `totalPages`, `onChange` | Paginated lists |

**Styling convention:** All components use Tailwind CSS classes directly — no CSS modules, no styled-components. Class arrays are joined with `.filter(Boolean).join(" ")`.

### Domain Components

Domain components live in subdirectories and receive all data via props from route loaders:

```typescript
// Route passes data down — components never call useLoaderData
<FlightCard
  flight={flightCardFlight}
  maxTakeoffWeightKg={2994}
  linkable={false}
/>
```

**Rule:** Components must NOT fetch data directly. All data comes from the route's `useLoaderData()` and is passed as props.

