## Permission Integration

### Route-Level Guards

Use [`requirePermission()`](app/utils/permissions.server.ts:46) in loaders/actions — it throws a redirect to `/login` if the user lacks the permission:

```typescript
const user = await requirePermission(request, "schedule:create");
// If we reach here, the user has the permission
```

For granular checks within an action, use [`hasPermission()`](app/utils/permissions.server.ts:135) and return 403:

```typescript
if (!(await hasPermission(Number(user.id), "schedule:approve"))) {
  return json({ error: "Forbidden" }, { status: 403 });
}
```

### UI Conditional Rendering

Pass permission booleans through `useLoaderData`:

```typescript
// Loader
const [canApprove, canPublish] = await Promise.all([
  hasPermission(Number(user.id), "schedule:approve"),
  hasPermission(Number(user.id), "schedule:publish"),
]);
return json({ canApprove, canPublish, ... });

// Component
const { canApprove, canPublish } = useLoaderData<LoaderData>();
{canApprove && <button>Approve</button>}
{canPublish && <button>Publish</button>}
```

**Permission naming convention:** `resource:action` (e.g., `schedule:create`, `booking:edit`, `finance:view`). See [`app/utils/constants.ts`](app/utils/constants.ts:38) for all permission constants.

