## Toast Notifications

Use the [`useToast()`](app/utils/toast.ts:51) hook from `app/utils/toast.ts`:

```typescript
import { useToast } from "../utils/toast";

function MyComponent() {
  const { showToast } = useToast();

  // Show toast in response to fetcher results
  useEffect(() => {
    if (fetcher.state === "idle" && fetcher.data) {
      const data = fetcher.data as { error?: string; success?: boolean };
      if (data.error) {
        showToast(data.error, "error");
      } else if (data.success) {
        showToast("Action completed", "success");
      }
    }
  }, [fetcher.state, fetcher.data]);
}
```

The toast system uses a global event emitter pattern — [`showToast()`](app/utils/toast.ts:35) can be called from anywhere, and the [`ToastContainer`](app/root.tsx:40) in the root layout renders the UI.

