## TypeScript Patterns

### Interface Definitions

Define loader data interfaces at the top of route files:

```typescript
interface FlightSummaryRow {
  id: number;
  flight_number: string;
  origin_code: string;
  destination_code: string;
  departure_time: string | null;
  status: string;
  // ...
}

interface LoaderData {
  schedule: Awaited<ReturnType<typeof scheduleRepository.findByDate>>;
  flights: FlightSummaryRow[];
  // ...
}
```

### Raw SQL Results

Cast raw SQL query results with `as unknown as Type[]`:

```typescript
const result = await db.query(`SELECT ...`, [params]);
flights = result.rows as unknown as FlightSummaryRow[];
```

### Component Props

Define props as inline types or exported interfaces:

```typescript
// Inline (for route-local components)
function DraggableBookingItem({ booking }: { booking: UnassignedBookingRow }) { ... }

// Exported (for shared components)
export interface FlightCardFlight { ... }
export default function FlightCard({ flight }: { flight: FlightCardFlight }) { ... }
```

