## Error Handling

### Global Error Boundary

The [`GlobalErrorBoundary`](app/components/GlobalErrorBoundary.tsx) handles uncaught errors at the app level. It distinguishes between:

- Route error responses (`isRouteErrorResponse`) — shows status code and data
- `Error` instances — shows message and stack trace
- Unknown errors — generic fallback

### Route-Level Error Boundaries

Export an `ErrorBoundary` from any route module to override the global handler:

```typescript
export function ErrorBoundary() {
  const error = useRouteError();
  // ... custom error UI
}
```

### Permission Errors

- `requirePermission()` throws a redirect to `/login` (302)
- Action-level permission checks return `json({ error }, { status: 403 })`

