## Best Practices

### Do's

- ✅ Use `requirePermission()` at the top of every loader and action
- ✅ Use the `intent` field + `switch(intent)` pattern for actions
- ✅ Define `LoaderData` interfaces at the top of route files
- ✅ Pass permission booleans through `useLoaderData` for conditional UI
- ✅ Use `useFetcher()` for non-navigation submissions (drag-and-drop, inline actions)
- ✅ Use `<Form>` for navigation-based submissions (approve, publish, delete)
- ✅ Save snapshots before optimistic updates and rollback on error
- ✅ Use `db.query()` for complex SQL and Prisma methods for simple CRUD
- ✅ Cast raw SQL results with `as unknown as Type[]`
- ✅ Use `useToast()` for user feedback on async operations
- ✅ Keep components pure — receive data via props, never call `useLoaderData` in components
- ✅ Use Tailwind CSS classes directly with `.filter(Boolean).join(" ")` pattern

### Don'ts

- ❌ Don't use CSS modules or styled-components — use Tailwind classes directly
- ❌ Don't fetch data in components — all data comes from route loaders
- ❌ Don't use role-based checks (`user.role === "admin"`) — use `hasPermission()` instead
- ❌ Don't create separate action handlers — use the `switch(intent)` pattern
- ❌ Don't use `fetch()` directly in components — use `useFetcher()` or `<Form>`
- ❌ Don't forget to wrap `<Outlet />` in layout routes
- ❌ Don't use `any` type — prefer `unknown` with proper casting
- ❌ Don't import server-only code (like `db`) in client components

