## Repository Pattern

### Structure & Conventions

Each repository is a **plain object with async methods** (not classes). Files live in [`app/utils/repositories/`](../../app/utils/repositories/).

**Naming conventions:**
- `booking.ts` — shared types + repository (can be imported client-side for types)
- `booking.server.ts` — server-only repository with write operations (imports from `booking.ts` for types)
- `flight.ts` — flight repository
- `checkin.ts` — checkin repository
- `schedule.server.ts` — schedule repository (server-only)
- `invoice.ts` — invoice repository
- `invoice-item.ts` — invoice item repository
- `booking-leg.server.ts` — booking leg repository (server-only)
- `admin.ts` — admin queries
- `aerodrome.ts` — aerodrome repository
- `aircraft.ts` — aircraft repository
- `bank-transaction.ts` — bank transaction repository
- `notification.ts` — notification repository
- `accounting-entry.ts` — accounting entry repository
- `export-log.ts` — export log repository
- `fare-route.ts` — fare route repository
- `flight-leg.ts` — flight leg repository

**Pattern:**
```ts
import { db } from "../db.server";

export interface MyRow {
  id: number;
  // ... column fields matching DB table
}

export const myRepository = {
  async findById(id: number): Promise<MyRow | null> {
    const result = await db.my_table.findUnique({ where: { id } });
    return (result as unknown as MyRow) ?? null;
  },

  async create(data: { ... }): Promise<MyRow> {
    const result = await db.my_table.create({ data });
    return result as unknown as MyRow;
  },
};
```

### Method Signatures

Common method patterns found across repositories:

| Method | Purpose | Example |
|--------|---------|---------|
| `findById(id)` | Single record by PK | [`bookingRepository.findById()`](../../app/utils/repositories/booking.ts:103) |
| `findByReference(ref)` | Single record by unique string | [`bookingRepository.findByReference()`](../../app/utils/repositories/booking.ts:110) |
| `findAll(page, pageSize)` | Paginated listing | [`bookingRepository.findAll()`](../../app/utils/repositories/booking.ts:184) |
| `findByStatus(status, page, pageSize)` | Filtered paginated listing | [`bookingRepository.findByStatus()`](../../app/utils/repositories/booking.ts:237) |
| `search(query, page, pageSize)` | ILIKE-based search | [`bookingRepository.search()`](../../app/utils/repositories/booking.ts:421) |
| `create(data)` | Insert a record | [`bookingRepository.createPending()`](../../app/utils/repositories/booking.ts:68) |
| `updateStatus(id, status)` | Update status field | [`bookingRepository.updateStatus()`](../../app/utils/repositories/booking.ts:117) |
| `updatePayment(id, data)` | Partial update | [`bookingRepository.updatePayment()`](../../app/utils/repositories/booking.ts:124) |
| `cancel(id, userId, reason?)` | Soft-delete / cancel | [`bookingRepository.cancel()`](../../app/utils/repositories/booking.ts:144) |
| `deleteFlight(id)` | Delete with cascade via transaction | [`flightRepository.deleteFlight()`](../../app/utils/repositories/flight.ts:193) |

### Return Types

Repositories define typed interfaces for their return shapes:

```ts
// Simple row type matching DB columns
export interface BookingRow {
  id: number;
  user_id: number;
  booking_reference: string;
  status: string;
  // ...
}

// Paginated result wrapper
export interface PaginatedResult {
  bookings: Array<{ ... }>;
  totalCount: number;
  page: number;
  totalPages: number;
}

// Extended row with joined data
export interface ScheduleWithStats extends ScheduleRow {
  flight_count: number;
  total_passengers: number;
  total_bookings: number;
}
```

