## Prisma ORM Usage

### Generated Client

The Prisma client is generated to [`generated/prisma/`](../../generated/prisma/) (not `node_modules/.prisma/`), configured in [`prisma/schema.prisma`](../../prisma/schema.prisma:6):

```prisma
generator client {
  provider = "prisma-client"
  output   = "../generated/prisma"
}
```

Import:
```ts
import { PrismaClient } from "../../generated/prisma/client";
// Or use the augmented db singleton:
import { db } from "../db.server";
```

### CRUD Operations

Model names in the Prisma client match **snake_case table names**:

```ts
// Find
const booking = await db.bookings.findUnique({ where: { id: 1 } });
const bookings = await db.bookings.findMany({ where: { status: "pending" } });

// Create
const booking = await db.bookings.create({
  data: {
    user_id: userId,
    booking_reference: "ABC12345",
    status: "pending",
  },
});

// Update
await db.bookings.update({
  where: { id: 1 },
  data: { status: "completed", updated_at: new Date() },
});

// Delete
await db.bookings.delete({ where: { id: 1 } });

// Count
const count = await db.bookings.count({ where: { status: "pending" } });
```

### Include / Select Relations

Use `include` for eager loading and `select` for projection:

```ts
// Include related data
const flight = await db.flights.findUnique({
  where: { id },
  include: {
    origin_aerodrome: { select: { code: true, name: true } },
    destination_aerodrome: { select: { code: true, name: true } },
    aircraft: { select: { registration: true, seat_count: true } },
  },
});

// Filtered include with take
const booking = await db.bookings.findMany({
  include: {
    booking_legs: {
      where: { leg_sequence: 1 },
      select: { origin_code: true, destination_code: true, leg_date: true },
      take: 1,
    },
    booking_passengers: {
      select: { first_name: true, last_name: true, email: true },
      orderBy: { id: "asc" },
      take: 1,
    },
  },
});
```

### Type Casting

Prisma results are cast to the typed interface using `as unknown as`:

```ts
// Single result
const result = await db.bookings.findUnique({ where: { id } });
return (result as unknown as BookingRow) ?? null;

// Array result
const rows = await db.bookings.findMany({ ... });
return rows.map((row) => row as unknown as BookingRow);

// Inline casting for nested includes
const rowWithLegs = row as unknown as typeof row & {
  booking_legs: Array<{ origin_code: string; destination_code: string; leg_date: Date }>;
};
```

### Transactions

Use [`$transaction`](https://www.prisma.io/docs/orm/prisma-client/queries/transactions) for operations that must succeed or fail together:

```ts
async deleteFlight(id: number): Promise<void> {
  await db.$transaction(async (tx) => {
    await tx.flight_legs.deleteMany({ where: { flight_id: id } });
    await tx.flights.delete({ where: { id } });
  });
}
```

