## Pagination

### Standard Pattern

All paginated repository methods follow this pattern ([`bookingRepository.findAll()`](../../app/utils/repositories/booking.ts:184)):

```ts
async findAll(page = 1, pageSize = 20): Promise<PaginatedResult> {
  const offset = (page - 1) * pageSize;

  const [totalCount, rows] = await Promise.all([
    db.bookings.count(),                              // ← separate count query
    db.bookings.findMany({
      skip: offset,                                    // ← offset for pagination
      take: pageSize,                                  // ← limit
      include: { ... },
      orderBy: { created_at: "desc" },
    }),
  ]);

  return {
    items: rows.map((row) => ({ ... })),
    totalCount,
    page,
    totalPages: Math.ceil(totalCount / pageSize),      // ← calculate total pages
  };
}
```

### Count + Data Pattern

For raw SQL pagination, run count and data queries in parallel with `Promise.all`:

```ts
const [countResult, dataResult] = await Promise.all([
  db.$queryRawUnsafe(`SELECT COUNT(*) as cnt FROM ...`, params),
  db.$queryRawUnsafe(`SELECT ... LIMIT $1 OFFSET $2`, pageSize, offset),
]);
const totalCount = Number((countResult[0] as { cnt: string | bigint })?.cnt ?? 0);
```

