## Error Handling

### Prisma Error Codes

Handle known Prisma errors by checking the `code` property:

```ts
try {
  const result = await db.bookings.create({ data: { ... } });
  return result as unknown as BookingRow;
} catch (err: unknown) {
  const prismaErr = err as { code?: string };
  // P2002 = unique constraint violation (e.g., booking reference collision)
  if (prismaErr.code === "P2002") {
    // Retry with a new reference
    continue;
  }
  throw err;
}
```

Common Prisma error codes:

| Code | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| `P2002` | Unique constraint violation |
| `P2025` | Record not found (update/delete on missing record) |
| `P2003` | Foreign key constraint violation |
| `P2014` | Required relation violation |

### Graceful Fallbacks

```ts
const result = await db.bookings.findUnique({ where: { id } });
return (result as unknown as BookingRow) ?? null;  // ← null if not found
```

