# Permission-Based Access Control & Audit

## Overview

This skill teaches you how to work with the FIGAS Remix project's **Permission-Based Access Control (PBAC)**, **authentication**, and **audit logging** infrastructure. Use this skill when you need to:

- Add permission checks to route loaders or actions
- Implement role assignment or revocation
- Query or create audit log entries
- Enforce Segregation of Duties (SoD) for financial controls
- Understand the dual auth system (legacy `users.role` + PBAC tables)
- Write code that checks user permissions for UI rendering

**Key files:**
- [`app/utils/auth.server.ts`](../../app/utils/auth.server.ts) — Session auth, `requireAuth()`, `getUserId()`, `getUserIdentity()`
- [`app/utils/permissions.server.ts`](../../app/utils/permissions.server.ts) — All PBAC functions, SoD, audit logging
- [`app/utils/constants.ts`](../../app/utils/constants.ts) — `Permission` object with all permission constants
- [`prisma/schema.prisma`](../../prisma/schema.prisma) — `roles`, `permissions`, `role_permissions`, `user_roles`, `audit_log` models (lines 1268–1356)
- [`prisma/migrate-users-to-pbac.ts`](../../prisma/migrate-users-to-pbac.ts) — Migration script from legacy roles to PBAC

---

## Authentication

### Session-Based Auth

Authentication uses **cookie sessions**. The session stores the user's ID after login.

```typescript
// app/utils/auth.server.ts:30-33
const session = await getSession(request.headers.get("Cookie"));
const userId = session.get("userId");
```

The session is managed via [`app/session.server.ts`](../../app/session.server.ts). Login sets `session.set("userId", user.id)` and logout destroys the session.

### requireAuth / getUserId

| Function | File:Line | Returns | Behavior |
|----------|-----------|---------|----------|
| [`getUserId(request)`](../../app/utils/auth.server.ts:27) | `auth.server.ts:27` | `string \| null` | Returns user ID or `null` if not authenticated |
| [`requireAuth(request)`](../../app/utils/auth.server.ts:38) | `auth.server.ts:38` | `string` | Throws `redirect("/login")` if not authenticated |
| [`requireRole(request, role)`](../../app/utils/auth.server.ts:96) | `auth.server.ts:96` | `PermissionUser` | Requires auth + specific role slug |
| [`requireAnyRole(request, roles[])`](../../app/utils/auth.server.ts:109) | `auth.server.ts:109` | `PermissionUser` | Requires auth + any of the listed roles |

### User Identity

The [`UserIdentity`](../../app/utils/auth.server.ts:12) interface provides backward-compatible user context:

```typescript
// app/utils/auth.server.ts:12-21
export interface UserIdentity {
  id: string;
  email: string;
  name: string;
  role: string;           // Legacy users.role column
  /** @deprecated Use `permissions` from PermissionUser instead. */
  roles: string[];        // PBAC role slugs (deprecated)
  /** @deprecated Use permission-based checks instead. */
  permissions: string[];  // PBAC permission strings (deprecated)
}
```

[`getUserIdentity(userId)`](../../app/utils/auth.server.ts:63) fetches both legacy and PBAC data, falling back gracefully if PBAC tables aren't populated.

### Post-Login Redirect

[`redirectToRoleHome(permissions, requestUrl?)`](../../app/utils/auth.server.ts:125) determines where to redirect after login based on permissions:

```typescript
// app/utils/auth.server.ts:139-147
if (permissions.includes("admin:access")) return "/admin";
if (permissions.includes("schedule:create") || permissions.includes("flight:view")) return "/operations";
if (permissions.includes("checkin:access")) return "/checkin/counter";
if (permissions.includes("flight:view")) return "/pilot";
if (permissions.includes("maintenance:view")) return "/engineer";
if (permissions.includes("finance:view")) return "/finance";
return "/bookings"; // fallback
```

