## Permission System

### Architecture (Tables)

The PBAC system uses five database tables defined in [`prisma/schema.prisma`](../../prisma/schema.prisma):

| Model | Line | Purpose | Key Fields |
|-------|------|---------|------------|
| [`roles`](../../prisma/schema.prisma:1269) | 1269 | Role definitions (containers for permissions) | `id`, `slug` (unique), `name`, `hierarchy_level`, `is_system` |
| [`permissions`](../../prisma/schema.prisma:1287) | 1287 | Individual permission definitions | `id`, `resource`, `action`, unique on `[resource, action]` |
| [`role_permissions`](../../prisma/schema.prisma:1301) | 1301 | Junction: which permissions a role grants | `role_id`, `permission_id`, unique on `[role_id, permission_id]` |
| [`user_roles`](../../prisma/schema.prisma:1317) | 1317 | Junction: which roles a user has | `user_id`, `role_id`, `assigned_by`, unique on `[user_id, role_id]` |
| [`audit_log`](../../prisma/schema.prisma:1335) | 1335 | Audit trail for all security-relevant actions | `actor_id`, `action`, `entity_type`, `entity_id`, `old_values` (JSONB), `new_values` (JSONB) |

**Key design principle:** Roles are **containers** for permissions, not authorization primitives. Always check permissions, not roles, in new code.

### Permission Format (`resource:action`)

Permissions use the format `resource:action` (e.g., `schedule:create`, `finance:reconcile`). This is parsed in [`hasPermission()`](../../app/utils/permissions.server.ts:147):

```typescript
// app/utils/permissions.server.ts:147
const [resource, action] = permission.split(":");
```

