## Permission Checks

### Route-Level Guards

Use [`requirePermission()`](../../app/utils/permissions.server.ts:46) in route loaders/actions to gate access:

```typescript
// app/routes/operations.schedule._index.tsx:121
export async function loader({ request }: LoaderFunctionArgs) {
  const user = await requirePermission(request, "schedule:create");
  // ... rest of loader
}
```

The function returns a [`PermissionUser`](../../app/utils/permissions.server.ts:7) object:

```typescript
// app/utils/permissions.server.ts:7-15
export interface PermissionUser {
  id: string;
  email: string;
  name: string;
  roles: { id: number; slug: string; name: string; hierarchyLevel: number }[];
  permissions: string[];
  /** @deprecated Use `permissions` directly. */
  hierarchyLevel: number;
}
```

**Available guard functions** (all in [`app/utils/permissions.server.ts`](../../app/utils/permissions.server.ts)):

| Function | Line | Behavior |
|----------|------|----------|
| [`requirePermission(request, permission)`](../../app/utils/permissions.server.ts:46) | 46 | Throws redirect if user lacks the specific permission |
| [`requireAnyPermission(request, permissions[])`](../../app/utils/permissions.server.ts:61) | 61 | Throws redirect if user lacks ALL listed permissions |
| [`requireAllPermissions(request, permissions[])`](../../app/utils/permissions.server.ts:77) | 77 | Throws redirect if user lacks ANY of the listed permissions |
| [`requireRole(request, roleSlug)`](../../app/utils/permissions.server.ts:98) | 98 | Backward-compat: checks `user_roles` table for role slug |
| [`requireAnyRole(request, roleSlugs[])`](../../app/utils/permissions.server.ts:114) | 114 | Backward-compat: checks for any matching role slug |

### Granular Checks

For finer-grained decisions within a route (e.g., showing/hiding UI elements), use [`hasPermission()`](../../app/utils/permissions.server.ts:135):

```typescript
// In a loader — pass boolean flags to the frontend
const canApprove = await hasPermission(Number(user.id), "schedule:approve");
const canPublish = await hasPermission(Number(user.id), "schedule:publish");

return json({
  canApprove,
  canPublish,
  // ... other data
});
```

**Important:** [`hasPermission()`](../../app/utils/permissions.server.ts:135) must only be called from loaders/actions, not from component render paths. It uses a single `EXISTS` query with request-scoped caching.

### UI Conditional Rendering

Pass boolean flags via `useLoaderData` for conditional rendering:

```typescript
// In the route component
const { canApprove, canPublish } = useLoaderData<typeof loader>();

return (
  <div>
    {canApprove && <button>Approve Schedule</button>}
    {canPublish && <button>Publish Schedule</button>}
  </div>
);
```

### Request-Scoped Caching

[`permissionCache`](../../app/utils/permissions.server.ts:19) is a `Map<string, string[]>` that caches permissions per request. It's cleared via [`clearPermissionCache(userId?)`](../../app/utils/permissions.server.ts:21):

```typescript
// app/utils/permissions.server.ts:19-27
const permissionCache = new Map<string, string[]>();

export function clearPermissionCache(userId?: number): void {
  if (userId) {
    permissionCache.delete(`user:${userId}`);
  } else {
    permissionCache.clear();
  }
}
```

