## Role Management

All role management functions are in [`app/utils/permissions.server.ts`](../../app/utils/permissions.server.ts) and require the actor to have the appropriate permission. They all create audit log entries automatically.

### Assign/Revoke Roles

| Function | Line | Required Permission | Description |
|----------|------|---------------------|-------------|
| [`assignRole(actorId, userId, roleId)`](../../app/utils/permissions.server.ts:263) | 263 | `user:assign-role` | Assigns role with SoD validation |
| [`revokeRole(actorId, userId, roleId)`](../../app/utils/permissions.server.ts:292) | 292 | `user:assign-role` | Removes role with audit logging |

```typescript
// Example: Assigning a role
await assignRole(actorId, targetUserId, roleId);
// Audit entry created: action="role.assigned", entityType="user_role"
// Permission cache cleared for target user
```

### Manage Permissions

| Function | Line | Required Permission | Description |
|----------|------|---------------------|-------------|
| [`addPermissionToRole(actorId, roleId, permissionId)`](../../app/utils/permissions.server.ts:318) | 318 | `role:manage-permissions` | Grants permission to a role |
| [`removePermissionFromRole(actorId, roleId, permissionId)`](../../app/utils/permissions.server.ts:342) | 342 | `role:manage-permissions` | Revokes permission from a role |

### Audit Trail

Every role/permission mutation creates an audit log entry via [`createAuditLogEntry()`](../../app/utils/permissions.server.ts:368). The audit entries use these action types:

| Action | When |
|--------|------|
| `role.assigned` | Role assigned to user |
| `role.revoked` | Role removed from user |
| `permission.granted` | Permission added to role |
| `permission.revoked` | Permission removed from role |

### Validation Helpers

| Function | Line | Description |
|----------|------|-------------|
| [`validateActorPermission(actorId, permission)`](../../app/utils/permissions.server.ts:480) | 480 | Throws if actor lacks required permission |
| [`validateRoleDeletion(roleId)`](../../app/utils/permissions.server.ts:463) | 463 | Throws if users are still assigned to the role |

