## Segregation of Duties

### Incompatible Pairs

Defined in [`INCOMPATIBLE_PERMISSIONS`](../../app/utils/permissions.server.ts:498) — a `ReadonlyArray<[string, string, string]>` where each entry is `[permA, permB, rationale]`:

```typescript
// app/utils/permissions.server.ts:498-502
const INCOMPATIBLE_PERMISSIONS: ReadonlyArray<[string, string, string]> = [
  ["finance:record-payment", "finance:reconcile", "Same person cannot record payments AND reconcile bank statements"],
  ["finance:create-invoice", "finance:record-payment", "Same person cannot create invoices AND record payments against them"],
  ["user:create", "user:assign-role", "Same person cannot create users AND assign them roles"],
];
```

### Validation Functions

| Function | Line | Description |
|----------|------|-------------|
| [`validateSoD(userId, permA, permB)`](../../app/utils/permissions.server.ts:508) | 508 | Checks a specific pair — throws if both held |
| [`validateAllSoD(userId)`](../../app/utils/permissions.server.ts:530) | 530 | Checks all known incompatible pairs — throws on first violation |
| [`validateSoDForRole(userId, roleId)`](../../app/utils/permissions.server.ts:550) | 550 | Checks before role assignment — prevents creating conflicts |

[`validateSoDForRole()`](../../app/utils/permissions.server.ts:550) is called automatically by [`assignRole()`](../../app/utils/permissions.server.ts:263). It checks:
1. Whether the role grants one permission of an incompatible pair while the user already has the other
2. Whether the role itself grants both permissions of an incompatible pair (self-conflict)

### Self-Approval Prevention

[`validateApproval(initiatorId, approverId)`](../../app/utils/permissions.server.ts:595) prevents users from approving their own actions:

```typescript
// app/utils/permissions.server.ts:595-604
export async function validateApproval(
  initiatorId: number,
  approverId: number
): Promise<void> {
  if (initiatorId === approverId) {
    throw new Error(
      "Self-approval is not permitted. A different user must approve this action."
    );
  }
}
```

