## Migration & Compatibility

### Legacy Column

The [`users`](../../prisma/schema.prisma:218) table still has the legacy `role` column:

```prisma
// prisma/schema.prisma:223
role  String  @default("passenger") @db.VarChar(50)
```

This column is **deprecated** but maintained for backward compatibility during the migration period.

### PBAC Migration Script

[`prisma/migrate-users-to-pbac.ts`](../../prisma/migrate-users-to-pbac.ts) migrates users from the legacy `role` column to the PBAC `user_roles` table:

- Maps legacy role values to PBAC role slugs (unknown roles fall back to `"passenger"`)
- Skips users who already have `user_roles` records (idempotent)
- Creates audit log entries with action `"user-role-migrated"`
- Usage: `node --env-file .env --import tsx prisma/migrate-users-to-pbac.ts`

### Deprecated APIs

The following are deprecated and should not be used in new code:

| API | Deprecation | Replacement |
|-----|-------------|-------------|
| [`UserRole`](../../app/utils/constants.ts:25) constants | `@deprecated` | [`Permission`](../../app/utils/constants.ts:38) constants |
| [`UserIdentity.roles`](../../app/utils/auth.server.ts:18) | `@deprecated` | `PermissionUser.permissions` |
| [`UserIdentity.permissions`](../../app/utils/auth.server.ts:20) | `@deprecated` | Use permission-based checks |
| [`requireRole()`](../../app/utils/permissions.server.ts:98) | Backward compat | [`requirePermission()`](../../app/utils/permissions.server.ts:46) |
| [`getUserRole()`](../../app/utils/auth.server.ts:52) | Backward compat | [`getUserRoles()`](../../app/utils/permissions.server.ts:188) |
| [`PermissionUser.hierarchyLevel`](../../app/utils/permissions.server.ts:14) | `@deprecated` | Use `permissions` directly |

